These are Puzzles for 4x4 Level 6

.:: Puzzle 4x4-Level-6-1::.
4 different games are played: backgammon, scrabble, bridge, snooker
The people have 4 different jobs:  firefighter, musician, scientist, writer
The people use 4 different means of transport: van, bike, bus, quad-bike
There are 4 different nationalities: colombian, egyptian, italian, japanese
 1. the person driving the quad-bike is on the left of the musician##1
 2. the writer is somewhere to the left of the egyptian##5
 3. the person playing backgammon is not the egyptian##6
 4. the person driving the bus is on the left or right of the person driving the bike##3
 5. the scientist is somewhere to the right of the person driving the quad-bike##5
 6. the writer is on the left or right of the person playing scrabble##3
 7. the person driving the van is the person playing backgammon##1
 8. the person playing backgammon is between the italian and the firefighter##2
 9. the colombian is on the left of the person driving the bus##1
10. the japanese is not the musician##6
11. the person playing scrabble is on the far left or far right##3
12. the person driving the quad-bike is in an odd position##4
13. the person playing bridge is the person driving the quad-bike##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |     2     |     3      |    4     |
| Beverage      | bridge     | backgammon      | snooker      | scrabble    |
| Food          | firefighter    | musician | writer | scientist     |
| Music-Genre   | quad-bike    | van     | bus    | bike     |
| Nationality   | japanese | colombian | italian    | egyptian |

